<TITLE> 41 assistant AGs resign </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 6 (bdnews24.com)Forty-one assistant attorneys general have submitted resignations. "They have resigned for re-structuring purposes, and many of them may be reinstated," attorney general Mahbubey Alam told reporters Monday. The assistant attorneys general submitted their separate resignation letters to Alam. The attorney general has accepted their resignation letters and will send them to the president through the law ministry, he said. As many as 58 assistant attorneys general were discharging their duties to date. An official of the attorney general's office said that the government was going to appoint a number of new assistant attorneys general soon. The resignation of the 41, who were appointed during the past BNP-Jamaat coalition government, will facilitate the new appointments, the official said requesting not to be named. bdn
